Quick Start


Here is an example of a very basic Tonis app. This will look familiar to many micro-frameworks.


?php

require __DIR__ . '/../vendor/autoload.php';

$app = new Tonis\App;
$app-
get('/', function($request, $response) {
    $response-
end('Hello from Tonis');
});

$server = Zend\Diactoros\Server::createServer($app, $_SERVER, $_GET, $_POST, $_COOKIE, $_FILES);
$server-
listen();




You can run it with:


php -S 127.0.0.1:8080 index.php


Then, load 
http://127.0.0.1:8080
 in a browser to see the output.


Mounted Middleware


This example shows how to mount middleware to an endpoint. You can use this technique to reuse middleware or mount
it to a different route.


$app    = new \Tonis\App;

// this will be executed for every request
$app-
add(function ($request, $response, $next) {
    $response-
write('pre' . PHP_EOL);
    $response = $next($request, $response);
    $response-
write('post' . PHP_EOL);

    return $response
});

$app-
get('/', function ($request, $response) {
    return $response-
write('GET on /');
});

// routers are middleware and may be mounted to the app
// additionally, they are reusable, and you can use them to create bundles/packages/modules
$router = $app-
router();
$router-
get('/', function ($request, $response) {
    return $response-
write('GET on /articles/');
});

// this mounts the router to /articles so the GET above will respond to /articles/
$app-
add('/articles', $router);




A 
GET
 request to 
/
 using the above app would return:


pre
GET on /
post




A 
GET
 request to 
/articles/
 using the above app would return:


pre
GET on /articles/
post




Tonis Project


For a more detailed example you can clone the 
Tonis Project
 which 
includes a recommended application skeleton.


Official Middleware


Check out the 
official middleware
 for some examples of middleware.

